fields.title: Give me content or give me death
fields.content:
## What's this all about?
At some point within the last 2 years, I was exposed to this idea that it is difficult to design without having _real_ content on hand. In fact, I believe it was presented more strongly: one _cannot_  design well without real content.

In other words, if you are designing a storefront for shoes, you need some images, descriptions, and marketing techniques that will be used to sell those shoes once the design is live.

## Take some time to think
I have pondered this idea at some length. I've had this conversation with a number of people. The overall consensus is that while the position has merits, it's often unrealistic. I've also, during this time, been involved in several design processes - to various degrees of success. 

Here's what I've come up with.

## Reality check
I agree that it is often not realistic to obtain enough content to really be able to design on a tight deadline using that content. I also agree that putting real content into proofs can be distracting when presenting said proofs to stakeholders. 

However, I also believe that having content first (and putting content first) is the right approach to design. In response to the latter problem, a design should be _presented_ and it should be the presenter's responsibility to coax the stakeholders away from getting enveloped in a tangential discussion about the merits of the content during that presentation. As for the former, I believe it is the designers responsibility to obtain the content by whatever means necessary and to not begin deigning until he or she has it.

## Content is king
As I said, I've been involved in several design processes during these ponderings - to varying degrees of success. This all comes from a place of realizing that most _frustrating_ redesigns (because not all redesigns are frustrating) could have been prevented by having some content on hand from the beginning. What's more, _accidentally_ awesome designs seem to have had real content available from the beginning.

So, give me content or give me death. And I simply won't start until I have it. Otherwise, the initial designs are likely to need to be killed anyway.
fields.blurb: As amusing as I find content generators like Hipster Ipsum, I don't believe they really help a designer in his or her travels. Fake content is a quick, lazy fix to a complex need. A web designer needs to put content first - above aesthetics, above search engine solutions, above deadlines. Without real content, it isn't really web design.

fields.title: A day with an iPhone
fields.content:
## On my way out the door
The wife asks, "aren't you bringing anything?" 

"I prefer to travel light."

In truth, I like to scope things out before bringing a bunch of crap along. I find it easier to be somewhere and remember to bring something for next time than to be bogged down with all kinds of stuff, wishing I didn't have it on me the first time.

Of course, I really should know better when the destination in question is a geeky, web/tech conference. The moment we walked in the entrance, I was surrounded by the familiar sea of glowing apple logos of Mac Book such-and-suches.

I also realized very quickly that I wanted to do some live-ish blogging during the event. So, two weeks into owning my very first iPhone, it was time to give the magic little device a run for its money.

## BarCamp Philly
BarCamps are conferences comprised of attendee-generated content. This past weekend, one was held in Philadelphia. Last year, it was recommended that I make sure to get there this year. It's hard for me to explain exactly how happy I am that I did.

At some point during the day, I [tweeted](http://twitter.com/brantsteen/status/127778107645108224) that these [the other attendees] were the types of people I had been looking to surround myself with for some time. And I meant it. This was a group of self-motivated, passionate, inspired, and inspiring people from all sorts of different areas of specialization. And, by and large, they were fairly close-by.

## Seize the day
I wanted to capture at least bits of the day. It seemed like the thing to do, considering how excited I was to be there. But all I had was an iPhone. Seemed like a challenge to me. It quickly became clear that I wanted to see just how much I could capture armed with just the phone.

### Tools of the trade
Here's what I used to stay productive through the day.

* Camera and Safari on the iPhone 4s
* [BarCamp Philly Schedule](http://s.barcampphilly.org/)
* [tumblr iPhone app](http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/tumblr/id305343404)
* [Twitter](http://itunes.apple.com/us/app/twitter/id333903271)

## Watch that battery drain!
I was recently talking to someone and I mentioned how the thing I was least impressed with on my new iPhone was the battery life. However, my real point in that conversation was that the only reason I wasn't impressed with the battery life was because I was holding to a ridiculous standard - that of the iPad (which clearly has more space to pack a tremendously larger battery).

At any rate, during the first talk, I noticed my battery tanking at an alarming rate. So, I needed to go into my settings and do things like turn the brightness way down and turn off location services. Additionally, I killed off any extra apps running in the background.

Part of me wanted to really push the limits and try to actually go all day without a charge. During the lunch break though, I ran into an open charger. My paranoia got the better of me and I took 20-25 minutes to give the phone about a 16% boost.

It should be mentioned that my brother's phone died before we even made it to the lunchbreak. As I said, when I say I'm not impressed with the iPhone's battery, it's because I'm holding it to an impossible standard. Clearly it's far better than most.

## The fruits of my labor
I took notes during each of the presentations I attended. Here's the links. 

* [Designing Co-op Games](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11788938165/notes-on-designing-co-op-games)
* [Podcasting!!](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11788938165/notes-on-designing-co-op-games)
* [Creating an Army of Brand Loyalists](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11785569894/notes-on-creating-an-army-of-brand-loyalists)
* [Building Better API Documentation](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11777237549/better-api-docs)
* [Hellban: Keeping Trolls Off Your Site](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11775213321/notes-from-how-to-get-trolls-off-your-site)
* [How to Win in Today's Startup Environment](http://brantsteen.tumblr.com/post/11773908675/notes-from-how-to-win-in-todays-startup-environment)

I took a little extra time on a desktop to clean up a few formatting things and add a couple links. By and large though, these posts are all straight from my phone, typed during the presentations.

## All and all
The iPhone is nothing short of impressive. After further reflection, I think I actually accmomplished _more_ with the iPhone than I would have with a laptop. There were less distractions than I normally face using a traditional computer, the need to conserve battery meant that I only flipped it on when I actually had something in particular to do, and it has a camera.

And as for BarCamp Philly, well, it was absolutely amazing and I can't wait for next year.
fields.blurb: I attended BarCamp Philly 2011, which was absolutely awesome, packing nothing but an iPhone. It's amazing how much productivity can be squeezed out of the thing.

fields.title: Python 2.7, libjpeg, PIL on OSX
fields.content:
The web is littered with people having the "jpeg_resync_to_restart" error, accompanied by a zillion walkthroughs of how to get libjpeg and PIL configured and installed on OSX. If your experience is anything like mine, though, none of those walkthrough seem to work.

So, here's another walkthrough, outlining what worked for me. Hopefully, it helps you too.

Delete all the old crap

You've probably been trying to install libjpeg and PIL for a few hours now, and there are likely remnants of various versions strewn throughout your computer. The first thing to do is get rid of all of that. Here's what I've found you'll need to remove.

cd /usr/local/include
sudo rm jpeglib.h
cd /usr/local/lib
sudo rm libjpeg*.*
cd /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/
sudo rm -R ./PIL
sudo rm PIL.pth

Notice that I am doing this in Python2.7 above. You'll need to change your directories a bit if you are doing this for some other version of python.

Update (3/20/2011):

I was trying to get PIL and libjpeg setup on a separate computer recently and I found that if you have installed PIL or libjpeg in the past (for previous versions of python) using MacPorts or something similar, you'll like have some libjpeg remnants scattered in some places other than those listed above.

I found that most of mine were sitting inside /opt/local/include and /opt/local/lib. However, to be more thorough, run this command:

find / -name *jpeg* -print

That will show you anything that even remotely smells of libjpeg. You can then delete selectively. 

Furthermore, I cleaned up my ~/.bash_profile to only include things on my PATH that I knew I wanted.

libjpeg

At this time of this post, the most recent version of libjpeg was 8c. Get it. Make sure you get the .tar.gz, the zip seems to be configured for windows. Once you have that, extract it and go into that directory.

Then, follow these instructions exactly.

export CC="gcc -arch i386"
./configure
make
sudo make install

Note: do not 'sudo' the ./configure OR the first make. That will blow it.

PIL

At the time of this post, the most recent version of PIL was 1.1.7. Get it, extract it, go into that directory.

Configure Setup.py

Open up 'setup.py', find the line that reads:

JPEG_ROOT = None

...and change it to:

JPEG_ROOT = libinclude("/usr/local")

From what I've gathered, that last step is actually no longer necessary. I've now done a couple installs of PIL without changing the JPEG_ROOT. If you comb through the source code, you'll see that the script will automatically look in /usr/local/lib, so adding it isn't really needed.

Install PIL

Save that file, head into the terminal in that directory and run the setup.

sudo python2.7 setup.py install

Notice that I am explicitly using the 'python2.7' instead of just 'python'. I doubt this really makes a difference, considering my 'python' is just a symlink to 'python2.7'. However, the iteration through all of this that it finally worked, I used python2.7 to run the setup and I'm a bit superstitious.

See if it works

To see if it all worked... run this command:

otool -L /Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/lib/python2.7/site-packages/PIL/_imaging.so

That should spit out a bunch of lines, one of which will reference your libjpeg. It will look something like this:

/usr/local/lib/libjpeg.8.dylib (compatibility version 12.0.0, current version 12.0.0)

If you get that line back, then chances are it all worked. If you don't see a reference to your libjpeg, something went wrong with the libjpeg configuration/installation.

To test it more definitively, open up a terminal and run the python command line.

python
import _imaging

No news is good news, the import shouldn't kick back any errors.

Hope this worked for you, good luck.
fields.blurb: It took me entirely too long to get the right set of steps together for installing libjpeg and PIL on OSX. It seemed worthwhile to write down.

fields.title: Using PIL to edit an image while maintaining the image's quality
fields.content:
Here's something that was bugging me for a while. It was one of those things that was just annoying enough to make me cringe whenever I saw the result but never important enough to fix.

At any rate, for some time I have been working on a project at my day-job where some simple server-side image manipulation was required. It's a Django project, so I've been using Python's PIL. All I was doing was some resizing and cropping.

When I first started using PIL, I noticed that I was getting some significant grainyness when saving an image. After a little poking around, I found that during image resizing, one can use an anti-aliasing filter.

import Image
img = Image.open("path/to/image.jpg")
img = img.resize((100,100),Image.ANTIALIAS)
img.save("path/to/new_image.jpg")

This somewhat cleared up the image quality issues I was having. It still wasn't great, mind you, but it was generally "good enough" and at the time, I needed to move on.

Months went by of looking at those resized images and being just ever-so-slightly annoyed; not enough to do anyhting about it but just enough to subconsciously cringe a little each time I saw one. Recently, I was revisiting that part of the project and decided it would be a good time to try to figure out how to maintain better image quality when using the PIL.

What I found (and what doesn't seem to be documented in the PIL's Image docs) is that one can pass a "quality" argument to the save method.

import Image
img = Image.open("path/to/image.jpg")
img = img.resize((100,100),Image.ANTIALIAS)
img.save("path/to/new_image.jpg",quality=100)

This is akin to dealing with the quality setting when saving a JPEG in photoshop. I learned this out after finding Djangosaur, which, by the way, is a damn cool name for a django blog.

It's somewhat tough to see the difference between antialias only and antialiased saved at 100 quality in the above examples. It's probably clearer in the picture of me than in the picture of the dog. However, it is a bit grainier, especially in larger images.
fields.blurb: Manipulating an image with Python and the Python Imaging Library (PIL) while maintaining the image's quality.

fields.title: Thoughts on the HTML5 logo
fields.content:
In case you've been living in a cave

The good

Well, I like the color and it looks good in black and white/grayscale. Also, it seems immediately "branded," so I don't imagine there will be much confusion when web-savvy folks see the logo.

The bad

It kind of looks like a 'S' and the smaller the logo gets, the more it looks like an 'S'. Logo's are supposed to scale well, I'm not sure this one pulls that off. Also, it reminds me of the Slomin shield.

The ugly

Simply put, it isn't. I don't find anything outright ugly or displeasing about the logo. Furthermore, it looks like it belongs on the web; like it belongs to a website. It has that web quality to it that seems to define a well-designed webapp logo. As it should, after all, it is a logo for a web technology.

By the way

I don't claim to be a logo designer or analyst but this seems like something worth talking about. So, take my opinions with a grain of salt, though I don't really think that disclaimer needs to be explicitly stated on a blog...

HTML5 has a logo now.

Your thoughts?

What are your thoughts on the logo? Please leave a comment and let me know.
fields.blurb: The new HTML5 logo has been released and I have some thoughts on its design. What are yours?

fields.title: My Resolutions, as a Web Professional
fields.content:
I thought I'd work up a list of resolutions and post it, so I can look back at it as the year goes on.

So, here they are, in no particular order.

  1. Improve my design capabilities
  2. Learn Ruby
  3. Learn Python Decorators (for some reason, this seems daunting to me. I just haven't sat down and looked at them very thoroughly.)
  4. Learn Django Tests, and use them

I'll go into each in a bit of detail.

Improve my design capabilities

I thought about wording this as "get better at design" but it didn't seem to quite accurately express what I'd like to do. I'm primarily a developer. I'm not a great designer. Depending on your point of view, this website might be a testament to that. However, I am consistently trying to improve.

So, to resolve that I would like to "get better at design" somewhat implies that to date, I haven't gotten better, that I haven't been trying to get better, or something else along those lines. In fact, I believe that I have improved over time, dramatically, and that I am consistently improving.

Instead, I resolve to improve my capabilities. I want to learn new ways to design. For example, I want to learn more about typography and color theory. These things will add to my designer tool box which, in turn, will help me continue to get better at design.

Learn Ruby

Last year, I delved into Python. This year, I'd like to learn Ruby. Just as I wish to expand my designer toolbox, I want to continue to expand my developer toolbox.

I'm not going to dive into Rails immediately. I plan on starting with haml and Sinatra, as I found some of their features appealing while reading this introductory tutorial. That said, my guess is that I will, in time, delve into Rails as well. It seems to be the web de-facto standard in the Ruby world.

So, I resolve to learn Ruby this year. The community looks like fun and the language looks interesting. Plus, it'll give me another heavy hitter for web development.

Learn Python Decorators

Well, the first two resolutions were my big ones. These next two are a bit more specific. As I mentioned, last year I delved into Python. Well, I still don't really understand how to write decorators. I resolve to tackle that this year.

Learn Django Tests, and use them

My greatest sin as a developer is likely that I do not do very much unit testing. Django, my current web framework of preference, has built-in testing mechanisms. Yet, here I am, not using them.

I resolve to learn how to use these tests effectively. I also resolve to actually use them.
fields.blurb: My 2011 New Year Resolutions. Trite, perhaps. Hackneyed, definitely. I'm going to write them up anyway.

fields.title: Adding Akismet to Django Comments
fields.content:
Despite Django's best efforts to use a honeypot-style spam filter, I have still had problems with spam entries using Django's built-in comment system. With a little poking around, I was able to find Django's documentation on the signals sent by their comments app. I've always had a good experience with Akismet when using WordPress and I'm quite fond of the service they provide. So, I figured I'd get Akismet hooked into my Django comments.

First, I used David Lynch's Akismet Python Library, which I found linked in Akismet's plugins and libraries. Then, I just modified his example to fit the Django framework.

I stuck the following code in my models:

from django.contrib.comments.signals import comment_will_be_posted
import akismet

def spam_check(sender, comment, request, **kwargs):
	akismet.USERAGENT = "David Lynch's Python library/1.0"

	my_api_key = "API KEY GOES HERE"    

	try:
		real_key = akismet.verify_key(my_api_key,"http://www.example.com")
		if real_key:
			is_spam = akismet.comment_check(my_api_key,"http://www.example.com",request.META['REMOTE_ADDR'], request.META['HTTP_USER_AGENT'],comment_content=comment.comment)
			if is_spam:
				return False
			else:
				return True
	except akismet.AkismetError, e:
		print 'Something went wrong, allowing comment'
		print e.response, e.statuscode
		return True
    
comment_will_be_posted.connect(spam_check,sender=Comment,dispatch_uid="comment_spam_check_akismet")

There are a couple things to note here. First, if the whole mechanism fails, I allow the comment to be posted. That way, if Akismet changes their API or something, the comments will still post (allowing spam) until i can get in there to update the code. Second, in practice, things like the API key should be placed in your settings file, then referenced as normal (settings.AKISMET_KEY or something).

If you are using a customized comments app, with Django's suggested mechanisms, you simply change the signal connection a little...

comment_will_be_posted.connect(spam_check,sender=CustomCommentModel,dispatch_uid="comment_spam_check_akismet")

I should mention that I didn't spend any time looking around to see if there was already a Django snippet out there to accomplish this. It was an easy enough implementation that it seemed like it was worth just writing it out myself.

If there's a more robust Akismet snippet for Django, I'd love to see it. Just post a link in the comments below (Now, with Akismet spam filter!).
fields.blurb: How to add an Akismet spam filter to Django's comments app.

fields.title: Microsoft Removes IE from Spoon Browser Sandbox
fields.content:
Despite the fact that I have recently discovered certain pleasures in the world of Apple, I do not plan to get in the habit of senselessly bashing Microsoft. I firmly believe that all sorts of industries (web, software, general computing) would never have developed as quickly without them. There is even an argument to be made that without Internet Explorer, other browsers wouldn't be nearly as innovative. With all of that said, this sort of thing pisses me off...

I may be a little late to the punch on this one but it would appear that Microsoft has requested that their browser no longer be available through Spoon Browse Sandbox. For those not in the know, Spoon offers a cloud service where people can use many versions (current and older) of all popular browsers. It's a service only available to PC users, as it requires a small plugin to be installed. I have relied on their service to test using a IE6 and a real IE7 (there are some major differences between real IE7 and the "emulated IE7" packaged inside IE8) for some time now.

Seems like a double blow... now it's going to be even more difficult testing in older IE versions and Spoon has become significantly less useful as a service. Admittedly, I haven't spent any time looking into why Microsoft has requested Spoon removing their browsers but I have a really hard time thinking of what a good reason for this would have been...
fields.blurb: Microsoft has requested that Spoon remove IE browsers from its browser selection.

fields.title: Django Quick Tip: Using Django's Redirects Middleware
fields.content:
If you are going to make use of Django's redirects middleware, make sure you have a 404.html inside the root of your templates directory.

If you don't, once you turn DEBUG to False (for use in a live environment), you'll end up with any redirects you have setup causing 500 internal server errors.

The reason for this is that the redirects middleware only triggers when a 404 is raised after mulling through url patterns. Part of raising that 404 is that Django looks for 404.html. If it doesn't find it and DEBUG=False, you'll end up with a 500 internal server error. However, the redirects will work find as long as DEBUG=True, which can cause quite a headache when moving a website live.
fields.blurb: A quick tip for using Django's redirects middleware in a live environment.

fields.title: Django: Adding inline formset rows without JavaScript
fields.content:
Django’s inline formsets are really quite powerful little things. In true Django-style, a few lines of code enables a user to edit multiple one-to-many relationships on a single page.

I am all about enhancing pages with JavaScript, don’t get me wrong. The keyword in that sentance, though, is “enhancing”. Pages should work without JavaScript enabled. This is hardly a revolutionary idea. More commonly it goes by the name of “Graceful Degredation” or “Progressive Enhancement”.

So, I was shocked when I found a complete lack of support when trying to add inline formsets without using JavaScript. There are many tutorials and ways to add them dynamically using JS (example, another example, a third example) but really nothing I was able to find giving a clear walkthrough of adding inline formset rows without it.

So, this tutorial is for people who want to add inline formset rows after incurring a page-reload while keeping the form’s entered data intact.

Well, as it turns out, it’s quite easy. Basically, you just modify the -TOTAL_FORMS field (a hidden field contained in the inline formset management_form) when the page is reloaded. The only tricky part is that request.POST data cannot be edited directly. Instead, we simply make a copy of that data, then use it for repopulating the page.

Lets say that we have a CarManufacturer that can make many CarModels. On that page, you have an ‘add’ button, which is actually a submit button for the form (there can be additional submit buttons with different names).

The template might look something like this:

<form method='post' action='{{request.path}}'>
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Car Models</legend>
      {{ car.management_form }}
      {% for form in car.forms %}
        <div>{{form.as_p}}</div>
      {% endfor %}
      <input title='Add a new car model' type='submit' name='add_car' value='Add' />
    </fieldset>
    <input title='Submit this form' type='submit' name='submit' value='Submit' />
</form>

Then, the view will look something like this:

# do whatever you need to get the car manufacturer
the_manufacturer = CarManufacturer.objects.get(pk=1)
 
# create the factory
AddCarFormset = inlineformset_factory(CarManufacturer,CarModel,extra=0)
 
# if this form has been submitted...
if request.method=='POST':
  if 'add_car' in request.POST:
    cp = request.POST.copy()
    cp['car-TOTAL_FORMS'] = int(cp['car-TOTAL_FORMS'])+ 1
    new_car = AddCarFormset(cp,prefix='car',instance=the_manufacturer)
  elif 'submit' in request.POST:
    # Do whatever you need to do on the actual form submission
    pass
 
# if this is a fresh form...
else:
    new_car = AddCarFormset (prefix='car',instance=the_manufacturer)
 
# return the rendered template
return render_to_response('the_template.html',{'car':new_car},context_instance=RequestContext(request))

That’s it. Just pass new_car to your template and use it as any other inline formset.

Don’t forget to leave a comment!
fields.blurb: Django's inline formsets are really quite powerful little things. This tutorial is for people who want to add inline formset rows after incurring a page-reload while keeping the form's entered data intact.

Это были плюсы …. 
А теперь о минусах!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! 
Сроки сорвали. Привезли диван ночью.А так как я работаю таксистом меня не было дома, жена приняла его и расписалась заплатила денег. А диван я собирался сам собрать.

НЕПЕРЕЗВОНИЛИ!!! 
На следующий день опять звоню!Мне в ответ:жена ваша расписалась в получении о том что претензий не имеет!Да? 
Смотреть-надо.Закон прав потребителя читали?НЕТ!?

Находят лохов.Впаривают некондицию.А в работу менеджеров входит динамить и отфутболивать!В работу-доставщиков привести ночью когда все спят и спарить!

fields.message:
Just wanted to say thanks very much for this: your solution worked for me when none of the (dozens of) others I looked at did.

If you're interested, I successfully used your instructions with Python 2.7.2 (the standard Apple build) on OS X 10.7.2 (Lion), PIL 1.1.7 and jpeg-8d. The only change I had to make was in terms of specifying the architecture: I used "x86_64" instead of "i386" for the libjpeg build (since Lion is comprehensively 64-bit).

Oh, & lastly, I dunno if it's worth mentioning, but you might want to just remind people at the top that they need to use an account with Admin permissions.

Thanks again!

fields.message:
Greetings,

I am the head of casting and partnerships for Mahalo.com, Inc. We have been creating innovative, educational content helping our users to "Learn Anything". We have recently entered the realm of mobile apps with over 20 applications in the App Store including "Learn Guitar", "Learn Pilates" and "Learn Garageband." 

I am interested in discussing the possibility of creating a video-lesson based, frontend developing app, built around your knowledge and expertise. This would be an opportunity to educate straight from the mind of a true expert, offering an unparalleled value in this rapidly growing medium. Mobile apps are quickly becoming the preferred way to consume content. In under six months we have seen 190k downloads, 165k updates, averaging 1.1k updates averaging every day. Users are loving learning with these devices and they are interacting and updating on a daily basis. We were also recently ranked amongst the top ten apps in the music and healthcare/fitness categories. 

This is not a sales pitch. We are not an app production company for-hire. We are interested creating an app that will serve as educational resource for anyone wanting to learn CSS, HTML5 etc. and we feel that your experience and expertise make you an ideal instructor. 

It is my intention to set up a call to discuss the possibilites. If you have any availability to get on the phone, please let me know. This is an opportunity to create something new, powerful and ultimately helpful to our users! 

Kind regards,

Andrew Cory Aikman
Mahalo.com, Inc.
310-593-6135 
cory@mahalo.com

fields.message:
Harmon Kardon computer speakers could be quickly attached to an HDTV with a Y-adapter to convert it output jacks right into a single jack which will use the speakers. The Harmon Kardon speakers are self-powered, therefore the HDTV won't face any power demands with the addition of additional sound. Because the computer speakers also have a subwoofer, low-frequency bass response ought to be improved within the integral speakers in it set. Insert the white and red plugs on the stereo cables to the left an right audio output jacks on the rear of the HDTV. Push the plugs on another end to the two large jacks on the Y-adapter. Connect the 3. 5mm plug on the finish of the Harmon Kardon subwoofer cable to the little jack on the Y-adapter. Plug the cables from the left and right Harmon Kardon computer speakers to the matching jacks on the rear of the subwoofer. Plug the subwoofer cord right into a wall outlet.
Resource:How to Hook Up Harmon Computer Speakers to an HDTV

fields.message:
With technology making rapid advances it has become possible to keep with the hobby of reading without the need of purchasing books. In the busy world of today seated in a single place with a book seems impossible. But with the advancement of technology the reader enables someone to read anytime, anywhere. Owning an reader enables someone to make use of the many titles that are offered on line at one's own convenience. You don't have to transport around big thick books anymore. So many titles are stored in that one single, slim device that may be carried around with the best of ease. Being in far flung places without any use of book stores or libraries isn't any bar to reading. All that's needed is is definitely an web connection and an eBook reader. Books are distributed around readers 24/7. ePaper technology allows the reader to see the pages just like if it's printed with no screen emitting any glare. It works on a battery and may be utilized indoors or out. To be able to read on line, it's important to down load the relevant computer software suitable for the computer and its own settings. Several soft ware can be found on line totally free. Besides the first outlay in acquiring an eBook reader, the hobby of reading do not need to be costly anymore. Purchasing a book costs so much and likely to the library means time and it might be unavailable. But, by using an eBook reader, a book might be downloaded at little cost and you will be on demand. It will likewise maybe not suffer lost or torn pages or in some instances, the increased loss of the book it self. Getting the books on line removes the requirement to have space taking bookshelves in the home as well as needing to preserve them. EBook readers really are a boon to differently abled persons for the reason that the adjustable fonts might help an individual with sight issues and programs are for sale to individuals with hearing defects too. The introduction of the reader helps to ensure that regardless of, what every one could have a book and become transported to different worlds via the written word. Printing of books needs paper and also to make paper you'll need to damage the environmental surroundings by reducing trees. Harm to the environment also does occur because of fuel fumes emitted throughout transportation. Disposal and storage of books and printing machinery involve costs. All this is often eradicated by reading on an eBook reader.

fields.message:
The Creative X-Fi Platinum is really a feature-rich sound card that incorporates many new enhancements over its predecessors. The powerful 24-bit X-Fi chip provides real-time enhancements to improve audio quality. If your X-Fi Platinum sound card isn't working correctly, you are able to identify and address some possible causes by troubleshooting these devices and settings. Audio Missing from Some Speakers Press the "Windows" and "R" keys simultaneously. This displays a Run box at the end of one's screen. Type "mmysys. cpl" in the Run box and press the "Enter" key. This loads the amount Get a grip on Panel. Double-click the "Speakers" icon and click on the "Sound Blaster" tab. Double-click the "Settings" button. This loads the Creative Audio Get a grip on Panel in your screen. Click on the "Speakers" tab. Click in the "Speaker Configuration" drop-down menu and choose the quantity of speakers attached to the body. Poor Sound Quality Press the "Windows" and "R" keys simultaneously. This loads a Run box. Type "mmsys. cpl" in the Run box and press the "Enter" key. This loads a Volume Get a grip on Panel in a brand new window in your screen. Double-click the "Speakers" icon after which click on the "Custom" tab. Take away the always check alongside "Digital Output Only. " Click on the "Levels Tab. " Lower the "Playback Control" slider to "75" or less. The audio device begins to distort at levels over 75. Click on the "Sound Blaster" tab. Click in the box alongside "Disable Sound Blaster Enhancements. " This disables features such as for example "Bass Boost, " which could cause poor sound quality on some speakers. No Sound Press the "Windows" and "R" keys simultaneously. This opens a Run box. Type "Devmgmt. msc" in the Run box and press the "Enter" key. This loads these devices Manager in a brand new window in your screen. Double-click "Sound, Video and Game Controllers" after which double-click "Create Soundblaster X-Fi Plantinum. " Consider the "Device Status" on the "General" tab. This box will tell you any detected issues with your device. If your problem is indicated in this box, take to reinstalling the drivers making use of your installation CD that included your card. Close these devices Manager. Press the "Windows" and "R" keys simultaneously to load a Run box. Type "mmsys. cpl" in the Run box and click on the "OK" button. This loads the amount Get a grip on Panel. Double-click the "Speakers" icon after which click on the "Custom" tab. Click to get rid of the sign in the box alongside "Digital Output Only" after which click "Apply. ".

fields.message:
Adobe Photoshop CS3 is among the most widely used graphics program on the planet. It has countless uses running a business, entertainment, and the media. Artists also utilize it for collage. A collage is an excellent method to present several photos or other pictures as just one image. It may be utilized in a scrapbook, a brochure or on an internet site. Developing a collage is simple to complete in the event that you have Photoshop CS3, even though these guidelines works with any version of Photoshop. Open Photoshop CS3. In the dialog box that opens, make the size and resolution settings anything you requirement for assembling your shed. For example, if you're placing this collage on the internet, you may make the resolution 72. But if you're having it printed professionally make the resolution at the very least 150. Name the document "Collage 1", and click "OK". Go directly to the Toolbar, and change the "Foreground" color to anything you want the backdrop color of one's collage to be. Then go directly to the "Fill" tool, and fill the canvas with the colour you picked. Open among the pictures you wish to increase the collage. Visit Select, and click "Select All". Then visit "Edit", after which "Copy". Finally, "Paste" the image in to "Collage 1". It will be by itself layer. Visit "Edit" after which Transform and choose "Scale" to resize the pasted image to whatever size you would like it to stay the collage, and "Rotate" to rotate it. Then make use of the "Move" tool to put it where you would like it. Repeat Step four with each one of the pictures you wish to increase the collage. Then visit "File", click "Save As" and from the listed file types save yourself the image as a PSD file. Finally, do that again, but save yourself the image as a higher resolution JPEG.
Cite: How to Make a Collage With Photoshop CS3

When I first setup my home studio I will recall mixing a song all night and then burn up a CD, go to my car, and be disappointed. Bad mixes really are a universal problem for many beginners. While music production computer software has several choices and features, the human hear may be the final judge of a great mix. Bad Mixes in many cases are a direct result poor hearing, however this is often changed with a few adjustments. Listed here are the largest mistakes newbies make when mixing music. Studio Monitors are the main culprit of bad mixes. You're going to get that which you purchase, so select a good group of studio monitors. Pick monitors from popular makes for optimal result. Where studio monitors aren't available, utilize four playback devices, headphones, house speakers, multimedia speakers and a subwoofer. Here is yet another mistake producers make when selecting a spot to set-up a house studio. Most Home Studios are setup in small rooms, frequently bedrooms and den areas. Small rooms create muddy mixes. Trying to mix your song in a little room will generate an imaging problem. Incorrect Imaging causes it to be hard for the ears to find out which instrument has been panned and correct panning creates clarity. My most useful advice is avoid mixing in rooms smaller than 6ft X 6ft. Yet another common mistake is Insufficient Soundproofing. Many newbies will either use soundproofing not enough or over-use it. Begin by Placing Studio foam behind your studio monitors, this can kill the echo from the leading end of one's room. Then, place an object just like a diffuser or bookshelf on the wall directly behind you as long as you're mixing your track, this will help you obviously hear the mid frequencies. Create bass traps for the studio. Bass traps will certainly reduce the reduced end rumble in your studio. Research you will discover lots of sites that will highlight how to set-up bass traps and soundproof your room. Each one of these recommendations will ensure better studio mixes later on.

fields.message:
Creating a DJ-style mix tape involves seamlessly blending one track to the next, usually maintaining the beat and tempo to ensure that people on the dance floor not have to prevent. Audacity, the most popular open-source audio mixing computer software, provides a few tools that permit you to fade in and out of songs and overlap them with techniques that express your very own style. Open Audacity by double-clicking on its icon in your desktop. Drop down the Files menu and choose "Open, " then see a first track you would like in your mix tape and click on the "Open" button. Audacity converts the file to a wave form which it draws from left to right over the screen. Drop down the Analyze menu and choose "Beat Finder. " Set the Threshold Percentage in the Beat Finder dialog box to 70 percent and click "OK. " Audacity creates a label track underneath the audio track, marking the major beats with a line. Drop down the File menu and choose "Import, " then "Audio. " See a 2nd track in your mix tape and click the "OK" button to import it. Click the 2nd audio track, then drop down the Edit menu and click "Select, " then "All. " Drop down the Analyze menu and choose "Beat Finder, " then "OK. " Audacity inserts another label track underneath the new audio track showing the beats as lines. Drop down the Tracks menu and choose "Sync-Lock Tracks. " This helps to ensure that whenever you move among the sound files, its corresponding beat label track will move with it. Click the Time Shift tool in the tool bar, then click the 2nd audio track and slide it to the best before end of the very first track is simply overlapping the start of the 2nd track. Align both tracks so the beat label lines at the conclusion of the very first track and the start of the 2nd track fall into line with one another. Click the Envelope tool in the tool bar; this causes blue lines to look at the very top and the underside of the sound files. The blue lines would be the track's volume "envelope. " In the very first track click the envelope at about the stage where you would like the track to start fading out. A white dot appears at that time. Produce a 2nd white point on the envelope at the end of the very first track. Click and hang on the 2nd point and drag the idea to the middle type of the track. The blue lines converge, "squeezing" the waveform between them and causing it to fade to silence. Create two points on the envelope of the 2nd track, one at the beginning and something where you would like the fade-in to prevent. Then drag down the idea at the start of the track to help make the two envelope lines converge. 0Click the green Play button to hear the resulting cross-fade. Make use of the Time Shift tool to regulate the positioning of the 2nd track as necessary. 1Import additional tracks in to Audacity, creating overlaps utilizing the Time Shift tool and cross-fades utilizing the same procedure. 2Drop down the File menu and choose "Export" to produce a new MP3 file with the mixed tracks.
Article resource: How to Make DJ Mixtapes in Audacity

The attribute making this very computer software better and various from others may be the fact, that it's non intrusive. A number of calendar options are for sale to PC users. calendar with bow image by Photoeyes from Fotolia. comCalendars are how a lot of us keep an eye on what events we have to attend, bills we have to pay, and tasks we have to complete. PC calenders particularly can be hugely helpful because they may be easily distributed to the others, printed out and perhaps synced with cellular devices such as for example PDAs and phones. If you're looking for PC calendar computer software there are numerous of different programs available. Microsoft Outlook Microsoft Outlook can be used in a number of domiciles and companies as both a calender programs and a contact program. Events within an Outlook calendar could be emailed to people in your address book and calenders could be distributed to contacts making scheduling business conferences easier to do since the meeting creator can immediately see if those they're inviting have a conflict. Calenders could be color-coded by topic for easy navigation and may also be synced with cellular devices to become taken on the run. Calendarscope Calendarscope is really a PC calendar program which allows users to produce color-coded calendars that may be synced over a number of different cellular devices including smartphones. The program lets users create daily to-do lists in addition to schedule daily, weekly, monthly and reoccurring events. A unique Task option allows users to see a summary of all their active tasks in addition to the ones that are overdue and people they've completed previously. Calendar Organizer Deluxe Calendar Organizer Deluxe is really a Windows calendar program that enables you to plan every thing from your personal to-do list to organizing a small company. Calendar Organizer Deluxe can display data as a conventional calendar or can make to-do lists that may then be printed and distributed to the others. fields.message: Robert Shapiro, a former US undersecretary for commerce, said it was market pressure that would lead to a change of tack in Europe - particularly when it comes to German Chancellor Angela Merkel. Shapiro, who served under former US President Bill Clinton and is currently an advisor to Obama, said the G20 summit was successful because the chancellor altered her position. Angela Merkel Merkel agreed to use eurozone funds to help Spain and Italy "For the first time, she agreed, begrudgingly, that the eurozone's money could be used to balance Spanish and Italian accounts," he told DW. Obama, along with leading politicians in the eurozone, has worked for months to convince Merkel to enact the measures necessary to prevent the euro's collapse, Shapiro said. Greek voters over the weekend narrowly lent their support to pro-bailout parties, which gives Merkel more room to maneuver, he added.

fields.message: стоимость имплантации зуба донецк титанокомпозит http://spletnicam.ru/wp-content/uploads/2009/05/237148_zu_2.jpg Хорошего дня. Вот, хочу поделиться Про болящий зуб . Случилось так, что я не очень давно был несколько дней в Донецке по делам службы, у меня оставалось 592 гривень до конца недели и чтоб вернуться домой, в мой родной город Северодонецк, как неожиданно я понял, что у меня болит зуб. Поначалу я решил перетерпеть, просидел первую ночь на найзе, на следующий день зуб болел, но было терпимо, а вот на вторую ночь я думал что умру, у меня катились слёзы, пакет со льдом почти не помогал,от полосканий зуб болел ещё сильнее, о том чтобы поспать и речи не было. С рассветом, как только стало чуть полегче, я принял решение сдаваться стоматологу. Поискавши по объявлениям, где можно вылечить зубы в Донецке, я обнаружил,что цены в клиниках Донецка не такие, как я ожидал, в большинстве Донецких стоматологий моих сбережений не хватит, чтобы вылечить зуб,не хватит ,чтобы поставить пломбу, а мне надо было ещё три дня на что то жить и ещё как то добираться домой. Вспомнив, как происходило лечение зубов во времена моей школьной юности, когда мне надо было ходить к зубному врачу по многу раз, а зуб стреляет все равно, я окончательно впал в депрессию. За завтраком, мой коллега ,заметив что я как то необычно кусаю, а я не мог прикусывать на больную челюсть, полюбопытствовал, что случилось. Когда он узнал, о проблеме, то рассмеялся и сообщил, что мне необычно повезло, что среди зубных врачей Донецка есть один, который с пониманием относится к ограниченным бюджетам государственных служащих, и что за решение похожей проблемы он заплатил примерно 240-250 гривень и уже пару лет на гарантии, и дал мне телефон 0954056453 и вэб адрес http://medeor.dn.ua/ . Я немедленно позвонил, внутренне опасаясь, вдруг моих денег не хватит и все подорожало или у того зубного врача не найдётся на меня времени, но время нашлось и ничего не подорожало. Не стану рассказывать про саму процедуру, я на ней был сам не свой, но когда отошёл укол осталось только желание отдохнуть, я смог нормально выспаться, назавтра же я проснулся с ощущением невероятного облегчения, зуб даже и не думал напоминать о себе, я знал, что там есть какая то пломба,или вкладка, но не ощущал её, и я мог нормально жеватьна эту сторону. Спасибо доктору Ковалёву Алексею, и стоматологической клинике "Медеор", мне кажется, это такая редкость в наши дни, так работать. А моя тётя, узнав что со мной произошло, хотела позвонить на телевидение и рассказать про этот случай, но ей там сказали, что это реклама. протез на аттачменах вылечить зубы донецк http://novostiua.net/uploads/posts/2012-05/1336220210_napitok.jpg

fields.message:
7. 1 surround sound speaker technology brings the giant screen movie experience directly into your family room. The 7. 1 speakers includes two front speakers, a center channel speaker, two rear speakers, two surround speakers and a subwoofer. This technology utilizes digital audio and some type of computer processor to put the listener at the middle point of the action. To be able to obtain the obtain the most of a 7. 1 surround audio system it's important to setup the speakers within their correct locations. Center Channel The middle channel speaker should be placed directly under your tv or projection screen. This speaker will handle the majority of the sound occurring in the heart of the picture such as for example dialogue. Front Speakers Position both front speakers to ensure that one is on each side of the tv, being attentive to the "left" and "right" designations. These speakers will give you a lot of the left-to-right stereo information and really should be raised to the height of the listener. Surround Speakers Both surround speakers should be positioned on the sides of the area, again being attentive to the "left" and "right" designations. These speakers will generate the spatial effect that simulates your situation in the action. These speakers are usually mounted at the top of the walls and angled slightly downward toward the ears of the listener. Rear Speakers Both rear speakers have to be placed behind the listener on the right left and right sides. Ideally the spacing between these speakers ought to be the identical to the spacing between your two front speakers. If they're mounted at the top of the walls ensure that they're angled downward towards the ears on the listener. Subwoofer The subwoofer accounts for generating the bass part of the sound spectrum. Bass is low-frequency sound meaning it's not directional. Because of this the normal subwoofer placement is generally near among the front speakers. Always place the subwoofer directly on the ground and not mount it on a wall or ceiling.
Article resource: 71 Surround Sound Speaker Advice
